\SPEECH<
\SPEAKER: Player King
\LINE: I do believe you think what now you speak;
\LINE: But what we do determine oft we break.
\LINE: Purpose is but the slave to memory,
\LINE: Of violent birth, but poor validity;
\LINE: Which now, like fruit unripe, sticks on the tree;
\LINE: But fall, unshaken, when they mellow be.
\LINE: Most necessary 'tis that we forget
\LINE: To pay ourselves what to ourselves is debt:
\LINE: What to ourselves in passion we propose,
\LINE: The passion ending, doth the purpose lose.
